People
Family
Law
Attorney
Henry
S.
Gornbein
Named
Of
Counsel
at
Lipson
Neilson
People
Family
Law
Attorney
Henry
S.
Gornbein
Named
Of
Counsel
at
Lipson
Neilson
By
Alex
Harring
-
March
23,
2021
6
Facebook
Twitter
Pinterest
WhatsApp
Henry
S.
Gornbein
//
Photo
courtesy
of
Lipson
Neilson
Henry
S.
Gornbein,
an
attorney
with
specialties
in
all
areas
has
family
law,
has
been
named
of
counsel
of
Lipson
Neilson
PC,
a
firm
with
offices
in
Bloomfield
Hills,
Grosse
Pointe,
Nevada,
Arizona,
and
Colorado.
Gornbein
is
a
former
chair
of
the
family
law
section
of
the
State
Bar
of
Michigan,
a
former
president
of
the
Michigan
chapter
of
the
American
Academy
of
Matrimonial
Lawyers,
and
a
former
chair
of
the
long-range
planning
committee
of
the
National
American
Academy
of
Matrimonial
Lawyers.
He
is
known
as
an
expert
in
understanding
social
media’s
role
in
divorces,
as
well
as
on
issues
such
as
wiretapping,
computer
hacking,
phone
tapping,
and
spycams.
In
addition
to
having
a
running
column
called
“Case
of
the
Issue”
in
the
Family
Law
Section
Journal
of
the
State
Bar
of
Michigan,
his
work
has
been
included
in
national
law
publications,
and
he
has
a
streaming
video
podcast
series
about
aging
parents
called
“Gracefully
Greying.”
Gornbein
has
also
written
the
book
“Divorce
Demystified,
Everything
You
Need
to
Know
Before
You
File
for
Divorce”
and
co-authored
“Child
Custody:
A
Complete
Guide
for
Parents.”
Lipson
Neilson
was
started
in
Detroit
in
1985.
